         I have two opinions on that thread link. I may tick people off with what I'm about to say too.</P><P>1) I have no business knowing any of the information that ex-guide said. She needs to take things up with Sony. She obviously has problems with them, and no matter what, we can't do much about it. We could quit sure, but does that really solve the problem? How many people here will really quit? Can I really do much for her besides feel pity? Let me go ahead and answer these ... no, not many, and no.</P><P>2) I was a mud admin back in the day. Those were player run only, for no money or monetary gain, and very little appreciation for what you did. I eventually ran a mud myself which only magnifies those problems. What Sony has here is a case of greed plain and simple. They see things they are doing, decide they can make money for it, and then get rid of the volunteer only people who were doing it in the first place. Cases in point; server moves, name changes, and soon to be ... premium support.</P><P>The only thing that will eventually cause things to come crashing down is when people no longer have a good time playing the game. Revenues will dry up and by then, CS as an issue will be too late. Sad but true, people buy games every day that have shitty support. Until EQ gets so bad it's not enjoyable, I don't really see Sony doing too much about it.</P><P>It's just a sad fact in the state of this gaming industry. :(</P><P>-Haytred</P><P><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=157027" target="_blank"><font color=red>Haytred Incarnate, 51 DE Heretic, Bristlebane</font id=red></a><BR><a href="http://www.iblackthorn.com" target="_blank"><font color=gold>Black Thorn</font id=gold></a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
